      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation protocol with analyst checklist; independent review of boundary condition setup.",
      "rationale": "A documented simulation protocol specifying boundary condition types, turbulence model settings, rotating reference frame configuration, and post-processing steps was followed for all cases. An independent analyst reviewed the OpenFOAM case directory setup for three representative cases. No use errors were identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification of model form selection (turbulence model, hemolysis model) with reference to published literature and sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model was selected based on published benchmarking for rotating turbomachinery flows. The modified Power-Law hemolysis model (Giersiepen coefficients updated per Heuser and Opitz) was selected based on comparative literature review. Sensitivity to turbulence model was assessed by comparison with k-ε results at the design point (RH difference 3.1%). Model form uncertainty is judged acceptable for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) characterised with uncertainty bounds; sensitivity of RH to input variation quantified.",
      "rationale": "Geometric inputs were derived from CMM measurements of three pump specimens with documented dimensional tolerances. Fluid properties (viscosity, density) were measured at test conditions. Inlet velocity profiles were derived from upstream flow conditioner characterisation. One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis across the 25-case DOE quantified RH sensitivity to geometric inputs. Input uncertainty contribution to RH was estimated at ±6% (k=1)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples representative of production device; material and dimensional conformance documented.",
      "rationale": "Three pump specimens manufactured to nominal drawing dimensions with documented CMM conformance reports were used for experimental testing. Specimens were fabricated from production-grade polycarbonate using the same tooling as the predicate device. Sample representativeness is judged adequate for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
